## The Cost of Paraphrasing

When you paraphrase:

- Claude guesses at the error type
- Searchable error codes disappear
- Stack trace context is gone
- Multiple exchanges waste tokens and time
- The fix may address a different error

When you copy verbatim:

- Claude sees exactly what you see
- Line numbers point to specific code
- Error codes match documentation
- First-response accuracy jumps

I've tracked this informally over months. Verbatim errors get fixed in one or two exchanges. Paraphrased ones take four or five, if they get fixed at all.

## The Bottom Line

Error messages are precise for a reason. They contain exactly the information needed to diagnose the problem.

Select everything from the error type to the last line of the stack trace. Copy it. Paste it into Claude exactly as it appears. Don't summarize. Don't paraphrase. Don't "clean it up."

The verbatim error contains the solution. Your summary hides it.
